      "side": 1,
      "message": "this seems incomplete; if the INI has `foo \u003d \"bar\"` or `foo \u003d \"bar with spaces\"`, we need to use `cue/literal.Unquote` to parse the input string value, stripping quotes and interpreting escape sequences.\n\nand when Unquote errors, such as with `foo \u003d bar`, you use the input string as-is, because it\u0027s unquoted.\n\nadd test cases for these too.",
      "revId": "f36fcb0cd7f87fe1fbfb0ba4e822d756bd00b650",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
